## Component Class Declaration Order

Always follow this top-to-bottom order:

```typescript
export class MyComponent {
  // INJECTED
  private someService = inject(SomeService);
  private fb = inject(FormBuilder);

  // INPUTS
  item = input.required<Item>();
  label = input<string>('');

  // OUTPUTS
  itemChange = output<Item>();

  // SIGNALS & CONSTANTS
  readonly MAX_ITEMS = 10;
  private state_ = signal<State>(initialState);

  // COMPUTED SIGNALS
  protected derived_ = computed(() => this.state_() * 2);

  // CREATE
  addItem(): void { }

  // READ
  getItemById(id: string): Item | undefined { }

  // DELETE
  removeItem(index: number): void { }

  // UPDATE
  updateItem(index: number, value: T): void { }

  // LIST
  get items(): Item[] { }
}
```

## Section Definitions

| Section | Contents |
|---------|----------|
| `// INJECTED` | All `inject()` calls |
| `// INPUTS` | `input()`, `input.required()` |
| `// OUTPUTS` | `output()` |
| `// SIGNALS & CONSTANTS` | `signal()`, `readonly` constants |
| `// COMPUTED SIGNALS` | `computed()` |

## CRDUL Method Groups

| Label | Intent | Examples |
|-------|--------|---------|
| `// CREATE` | Add new items | `addItem`, `addUnit` |
| `// READ` | Return single value | `getById`, getters |
| `// DELETE` | Remove items | `removeItem`, `removeUnit` |
| `// UPDATE` | Modify existing state | `updateItem`, `toggleType` |
| `// LIST` | Return collections | `get items()`, `get units()` |

- Private helpers that don't fit CRDUL → place under nearest related section or `// HELPERS`
- Keep sections in order even if a section has only one method
- Omit empty sections entirely (except always keep `// INJECTED` if the class has any injections)
